data.description: Check out this Slaughter address, located in the award winning Zachary School District.  This two story home is situated on two beautiful acres, with a gorgeous, tree lined driveway, and a metal workshop with a loft, tons of storage and RV/boat port.  You will love the glassed-in porch, which contains a separate office, a welded grill and burner, which vents through the chimney (this is a one of a kind, must see)!  The porch overlooks the patio, with charming clay tiles and a lovely garden, with a picket fence, fountain, pic-nic tables and an arbor.  Inside, the first level includes a spacious living room with a dining nook and bay window, a beautiful raised brick hearth that covers one wall.  The kitchen has granite countertops and a moveable island for easy entertaining.  You will also find a large master bedroom on this level, a walk-in laundry room and a full bath.  Three HUGE bedrooms await you upstairs with closet space galore and one full bath.  The largest bedroom upstairs offers built in dressing areas and mounted mirrors.  Beautiful views await you from all windows, plus a “Bonus” guest suite on the first floor with a separate entrance, containing two bedrooms and a living area.  Outside you will find a new hot water heater, two HVAC units and multiple storage buildings (These three storage units are negotiable).  This is country living at its finest with all the conveniences of town just minutes away.  Call today to tour this roomy home and expansive acreage.
